        "id": 2958356,
        "name": null,
        "username": "TomHill",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/t/edb3f5/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2020-08-16T22:12:14.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Took this to dinner w/ friends last night:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<strong>Ch.Coutet a Barsac PremierCruClasse AC: Barsac (MeBaC; 11%-14%) 1976</strong>: Deep golden/burnished bronze color; fairlt strong peachy/apricotty/botrytis light cedary/pencilly/oak/cigar box rather complex old-Sauternes lovely nose; fairly tart off-dry/some dried out very strong pencilly/cedary/oak some peachy/apricotty/botrytis some bitter/dried-out fairly complex finish; very long/lingering strong cigar box/cedary/pencilly some botrytis/peachy/apricotty finish; a lovely complex old Sauternes but pretty dried out &amp; a bit bitter; not a great example of an old Sauternes.</li>\n</ol>\n<hr>\n<p>A wee BloodyPulpit:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>I took this wine to accompany a delicious LemonMousse as the dessert course. It didn\u2019t have the sweetness to hold up to the dessert. It is more an apertif wine than a dessert wine.<br>\nTom</li>\n</ol>",
